# =================================
# 📋 STEP-BY-STEP SETUP GUIDE
# =================================

# 1. STRIPE SETUP:
#    - Go to https://dashboard.stripe.com/apikeys
#    - Copy LIVE keys (not test keys)
#    - Create products with weekly/annual pricing
#    - Note down price IDs

# 2. FIREBASE SETUP:
#    - Go to https://console.firebase.google.com/
#    - Create production project
#    - Enable Authentication → Email/Password
#    - Generate service account key (downloads JSON)
#    - IMPORTANT: Copy private_key from JSON exactly with line breaks
#    - Don't use quotes or \n escape sequences in Railway
#    - Copy project config for frontend

# 3. SESSION SECRET:
#    - Generate: openssl rand -hex 32
#    - Must be 32+ characters

# 4. RAILWAY POSTGRESQL:
#    - Add PostgreSQL plugin in Railway dashboard
#    - DATABASE_URL auto-populated

# 5. WEBHOOK SETUP (after deployment):
#    - Get Railway URL: https://your-app.up.railway.app
#    - Add webhook in Stripe: /api/stripe-webhook
#    - Copy webhook secret to STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# =================================
# ✅ VALIDATION COMMANDS
# =================================

# After setting variables, test:
# curl https://your-app.up.railway.app/health
# curl https://your-app.up.railway.app/api/deployment-info

# =================================
# 🚨 SECURITY NOTES
# =================================

# - Use LIVE Stripe keys in production
# - Use production Firebase project
# - Generate unique SESSION_SECRET
# - Never commit secrets to git
# - Firebase private key must include \n newlines
# - All VITE_ variables are PUBLIC (client-side)